## 5. SUBSCRIPTION EDGE CASES

### Scenario: Club owner deletes club while subscription is active
- Required handling: `delete-club` flow must cancel Stripe subscription before deleting club row.
- Cascade: `club_subscriptions` has `ON DELETE CASCADE` — row auto-deleted when club deleted. But Stripe subscription must be cancelled first via API call.

### Scenario: Stripe webhook delivers the same event twice
- Prevention: `stripe-webhook` uses upsert on `stripe_subscription_id`. Idempotent by design.
- Required: do NOT use INSERT without ON CONFLICT handling in `stripe-webhook`.

### Scenario: Subscription goes `past_due` while games are scheduled
- Required handling: existing games remain active. New paid game creation is blocked.
- UI: show upgrade/payment prompt in club owner settings. Do NOT delete or cancel existing games.

### Scenario: Club downgrades from pro to free mid-billing period
- Required handling: retain all existing data. Block new paid game creation. Existing paid bookings continue.
- Do NOT cancel existing bookings on downgrade.

